      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Taking an extra dose of lisinopril isn't just cautious—it's potentially dangerous. While your medication aims to keep your blood pressure steady, doubling up can cause a dangerous spike in blood pressure, not a decrease. The risk of side effects like dizziness, shortness of breath, or even a hypertensive crisis far outweighs the temporary benefit of a \"catch-up\" dose. Stick to your prescribed schedule. If you miss a dose, wait until the next one, not double up. Your safety is the priority, and there's no room for guesswork when it comes to medication.",
